**VPN vs. messaging**

All Tails workers met earlier this year to plan improvements to the product and
the project. We decided to introduce one big feature this year, but can’t pick
between bringing VPN functionality to Tails or adding messaging tools.

Help us decide by sharing your preference in this survey:
https://survey.tails.boum.org/index.php/184541

We'll do the losing option next!

**Tails.net**

Tails has a cool, new domain: tails.net.

After 14 years of using a subdomain of `boum.org` , we finally found a new home
that will be easier for everybody to remember and type.

`tails.boum.org` will continue working while we migrate. Thank you to
`boum.org` , for supporting us all these years. Their support was and continues
to be very valuable!

**What we’re reading**

* In India, the state of Manipur has spiralled into intense communal and ethnic
  conflict. A 3-month internet shutdown led to the silencing of the minority Kuki
  community. Internet access was permitted for people with broadband connections
  who undertook to only use static IP and not use any VPNs. Mobile internet
  remains inaccessible, and is the dominant way to access the internet for the
  Kuki community. The dystopian [undertaking](https://i.redd.it/g329xvb6ueeb1.jpg)
  makes for a ~~fun~~ chilling read.

* In this article from 15 years ago, Cory Doctorow decries the intrusive data
  collection tendencies of law enforcement around the word. A seasoned advocate
  of individuals’ privacy rights and critic of surveillance capitalism, he argues
  that law enforcement doesn't know what to do with the data it already has. As
  countries around the world lust after collecting more and more data, this
  article is both prescient and timeless:
  https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2008/jun/17/surveillance.database

* And here’s something to keep an eye out for. A guide is being built to resist
  the weaponization of digital tools by using some of your own:
  https://www.anarsec.guide/
